00:00:00,110 --> 00:00:03,980
In this video, we are going to learn how gRPC works.

2
00:00:04,850 --> 00:00:11,510
A RPC is a form of client server communication that uses a function called, rather than usual Http

3
00:00:11,510 --> 00:00:11,810
call.

4
00:00:11,810 --> 00:00:17,990
So in gRPC, a client application can directly call a method on a server application on a different

5
00:00:17,990 --> 00:00:24,380
machine like it is a local object, it making it easy for you to build distributed applications and

6
00:00:24,380 --> 00:00:25,190
services.

7
00:00:26,460 --> 00:00:33,960
As with many RPC systems, gRPC is based on the idea of defining a service that specifies methods,

8
00:00:33,960 --> 00:00:38,940
and these can be called remotely with their parameters and return types.

9
00:00:38,940 --> 00:00:45,810
On the server side, the server implements this interface and runs a gRPC server to handle client calls.

10
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:52,110
On the client side, the client has a setup that provides the same methods as the server.

11
00:00:53,490 --> 00:00:59,970
gRPC client and servers can work and talk to each other in a different of environments, from servers

12
00:00:59,970 --> 00:01:06,570
to your own desktop applications, and that can be written in any language that gRPC supports.

